    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Game in which a heavy ball is rolled down a long, narrow lane called an alley toward ten pins, the aim being to knock down more pins than an opponent. The game is quite different from the sport of bowls, or lawn bowls, in which the aim is to bring the ball to rest near a stationary ball called the jack.</Note_Text>
